 By Theodore Opara ENGINEERS from Jaguar Land Rover are working on the next generation of protective workplace clothing – a lightweight 3D-printed glove which could help better protect employees from the threat of a musculoskeletal disorder. The 3D glove is designed for people working on the production line, for example those required to fit clips or fasteners into the chassis during assembly of Jaguar and Land Rover’s luxury vehicles. Continue reading JLR engineers research on solution to musculoskeletal disorder at Vanguard Nigeria. Source: Vanguard